8) pulmonary fibrosis → disease  

Regulatory relationships (directly stated/supported by the abstract):  
• PM2.5 downregulates ALKBH5  
• ALKBH5 reduces N6-methyladenosine (with a secondary effect decreasing Atg13)  
• N6-methyladenosine is on Atg13  
• Atg13 forms ULK complex  
• ULK complex upregulates autophagy  
• ULK complex upregulates inflammation  
• Inflammation promotes pulmonary fibrosis  
• PM2.5 upregulates autophagy  

